Myrtle Beach was awesome. I went with my dad, my sisters, my aunt, uncle, and my 2 cousins. I was there from august 16 to the 23. Doodles and I went down a day earlier with my aunt and her crew  b/c my dads car would of been to squished.

The thing i luv most about myrtle is u step out of ur hotel lobby and a few yards away is a pool, with a little beach bar and grill, and then there are sum steps and ur on the beach. It's great and the hotel is awesome it has a whole kitchen and bedrooms. so sum nights u can stay on the beach longer and u can eat dinner in . The hotel we stay at is its own hotel/Condo's but, u go through a company called the "Caravbelle" to rent the room b/c ppl own each room. But, there are 6 other hotels that are part of the "Caravelle" so u get to use all those pools and things offered in at that hotel. So that was fun going in the ocean and then going straight to a pool. And if u wanted to go to ur room b/c u forgot sumthing it was right there for u.

The waves there are incredible as well. They knock u right over. And the beaches up here dont have like that nice sand lol. The sand there is hot but, it is all sand there are no rocks or anything in it. The only place there are little baby rocks and a few shells is as soon as u walk in the water and they are very minor like if u walk on them they dont hurt, buty i learned that if u fall hard on them u get wounded. lmao. I was boarding and the wave brought me close to the shore and i stood up and i was walking back out and all of a sudden i lost my balance b/c of another wave and in front of tons of ppl i fall like a dumb ass and cut the top of my thigh kinda near my hip . And it was bleeding and it really hurt. So my cousin and i went up to the lifeguard, and i showed him and i was like do u have a bandage and hes like "NAH got nuttin like that" with a little southern accent. lol He was cute but, I mean he didnt even have a 1st aid kit and hes a lifeguard. lol. 

The whole week we (sisters and i ) notice this french speaking family from Canada thAT was there last year as well. And we wanted to talk to them so bad b/c there was a 14 yr old boy, 13 yr old boy, 8 yr old boy, and a 6 yr old girl. We thought we could practice sum french, but we learned from Allison (meeting the 13 yr-old one in the water) that him and his older brother know english well, and the little ones are just learning.So on our last day we were determined to become friends, b/c the boys were so Hot and they seemed fun lol. And it happened we were with the little two all day talking in french, in a little english and it really was funny and cool. So the next day they were leaving early i nthe morning and so were we, and i lookedo ut on the balcony and i couldnt see their car so I was kinda sad b/c we didnt even get to say bye. But, as amanda and ali were going down in the elevator the oldest boy got in as well. It was great, b/c we got to say goodbye and all this stuff lol. So i walk out and the oldest, 3rd youngest, and the youngest are there in the lobby and they are talking to me and the whole time in my head I'm like "Iluv this family". So a few minutes b4 they drove away their mom gave us their number, address, and the oldest boys email address lol. The mother told me I could come to Canada and visit them. 

It was just a great trip and when I got home, I couldnt believe how much reality was setting in. Especially b/c of school and summer reading. I only finsished one book and i have done 2 chapters in the second book! o well lol.

well g2g ttyl!
